ABUJA  – The Senate Minority Caucus on Fri­day reacted to President Muhammadu Buhari’s New Year speech. The President has, in his New Year address promised to address issues be­deviling the nation. But, reacting to the address, the Caucus, in a statement by the Mi­nority Leader, Senator Enyinnaya Abaribe, told Mr. President to face governance and stop making excuses at every turn. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! Abaribe also said that the legisla­ture, particularly the minority caucus is ready to cooperate with the presi­dency in any sincere and genuine ef­fort to tackle insecurity in the country and keep the people safe. “Nonetheless, President Mu­hammadu Buhari must as a fact face governance and stop making excuses at every turn, especially his penchant at making references to 2015 as reasons why he fails to perform. It does not end at making broadcast, but in exhibiting genu­ine seriousness in governance for all Nigerians. New Year Tragedy: Bus Driver Shot Dead In Benin Volkswagen Mechanic Shot Dead In Benin “The President is elected to pro­vide governance, by so doing he must be ready to proffer solutions, right wrongs where they exist and solve problems besetting the country in every facet and not always relapse to advancing excuses to explain away palpable failures. “As for us in the minority caucus, we are willing as always to cooperate with the presidency in any sincere and genuine effort to provide good gover­nance to Nigerians,” he said. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION